_legacy_capabilities.notes: Wiki Source. by individuals' names (at least if you're logged in with Sastre's account). Individuals' pages on companyhouse.de should list all past and current affiliations as a director ("Geschäftsführer") or "Prokurist" ("authorized signatory"), as well as their date of birth and (most recent) place of residence. Ownership relationships aren't usually listed (though occasionally they are, especially for KG companies). The date of birth listed on companyhouse.de is reliable, but the dates of affiliations are very unreliable, so affiliations should ideally be confirmed on unternehmensregister.de as outlined above, if you're going to mention them in a report. There's no simple way to search for companies that a person owns; the best approach is to use Unternehmensregister.de to check the ownership of any companies where the subject is a director, or where you have other reason to suspect a connection.
